OSS Core Library build system is based on the sipXecs (http://www.sipfoundry.org)

Prerequisites (CentOS or Fedora)
- Install oss_externals from the http://bridge.ossapp.com repository 
  - cd /etc/yum.repos.d
  - CentOS:  wget http://bridge.ossapp.com/karoo/repo/1.5.0/stage/karoo-1.5.0-centos.repo
  - Fedora:  wget http://bridge.ossapp.com/karoo/repo/1.5.0/stage/karoo-1.5.0-fedora.repo
  - yum update
  - yum install oss_externals-devel

Building From Source (CentOS or Fedora)
- Download the source code from https://github.com/joegen/oss_core and build it
	- git clone https://github.com/joegen/oss_core.git
	- cd oss_core/
	- autoreconf -if
	- mkdir -p .build
	- cd .build
	- ../configure --prefix=`pwd`/root
	- make oss
	
Building RPMS (CentOS or Fedora)
- Create RPM Build environment
	- echo "%_topdir      $HOME/rpmbuild" >> ~/.rpmmacros
	- mkdir -p ~/rpmbuild/{BUILD,SOURCES,RPMS,SRPMS,SPECS}
	- cd oss_core/
	- autoreconf -if
	- mkdir -p .rpmbuild
	- cd .rpmbuild
	- ../configure --enable-rpm \
	--with-yum-proxy=http://localhost:3128 \
	CENTOS_BASE_URL="http://ftp.jaist.ac.jp/pub/Linux/CentOS"  \
	FEDORA_BASE_URL="http://ftp.jaist.ac.jp/pub/Linux/Fedora"} \
	MIRROR_SITE="http://ftp.linux.ncsu.edu/pub" \
	FEDORA_ARCHIVE_BASE_URL="http://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/archive/fedora/linux"
- Create chroots for Mock (https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Projects/Mock)
	- sudo usermod -a -G mock $USER
	-	CentOS_5: make distro.centos-5-x86_64.repo-chroot-init
	-	CentOS_6: make distro.centos-6-x86_64.repo-chroot-init
	-	Fedora_16: make distro.fedora-16-x86_64.repo-chroot-init
- Building the RPMS
	-	CentOS_5: make distro.centos-5-x86_64.oss_core.rpm
	-	CentOS_6: make distro.centos-6-x86_64.oss_core.rpm
	-	Fedora_16: make distro.fedora-16-x86_64.oss_core.rpm

	


	

